Dashboard Overview

The Supply Chain Analytics Dashboard was developed using Power BI and connected directly to Snowflake to provide real-time business insights. The dashboard helps analyze product sales, delivery performance, shipping efficiency, and customer segmentation. Interactive filters allow users to explore data across different regions and categories, supporting data-driven decision-making.

Dashboard Components

1. Sales Analysis

This visualization analyzes sales performance across different product categories and regions. It helps identify the most profitable product categories and understand regional sales trends.

Key Insights:
Compare sales across categories.
Identify top-performing product groups.
Analyze regional sales contribution.

2. Shipping Mode Analysis

This visualization compares sales and order distribution across different shipping methods such as Standard Class, First Class, Second Class, and Same Day delivery.

Key Insights:
Evaluate shipping method performance.
Understand customer shipping preferences.
Compare sales generated through each shipping mode.

3. Delivery Performance Analysis

This donut chart provides a summary of delivery statuses including Late Delivery, Advance Shipping, Shipping on Time, and Shipping Cancelled.

Key Insights:
Monitor delivery efficiency.
Identify delayed shipments.
Measure overall logistics performance.

4. Customer Segment Analysis

This treemap visualizes sales distribution among different customer segments such as Consumer, Corporate, and Home Office.

Key Insights:
Identify high-value customer segments.
Understand customer purchasing behavior.
Support customer-focused business strategies.

5. Region Slicer

The dashboard includes an interactive Order Region Slicer that allows users to filter all visualizations based on specific regions.

Benefits:
Dynamic dashboard filtering.
Region-specific analysis.
Improved user interaction and reporting flexibility.


Business Value
The dashboard enables organizations to:
Monitor supply chain performance.
Improve delivery operations.
Identify profitable product categories.
Analyze customer behavior.
Support strategic business decisions through data-driven insights.

The dashboard successfully integrates Snowflake and Power BI to transform raw supply chain data into meaningful business insights. By providing interactive visualizations and real-time analytics, the solution helps improve operational efficiency, customer satisfaction, and overall business performance.
